Lagrangian description 

To overcome the ambiguities, intrinsically concerned with the
bootstrap scenario, the lagrangian approach proves to be an
alternative route.

The Euclidean action, describing the bulk dynamics, is that of
free massless symplectic fermions(A careful study of  the
symplectic fermions at the critical point may be found in
.) , supplemented by a mass term
 
, which are zero dimensional anti-commuting fields
( and ), belong to the same doublet,
characterized by mass , while  is an
antisymmetric tensor. A detailed analysis of the bulk system,
including mode expansions of the basic fields, commutation
relations and charge conjugation properties, can be found in the
Appendix A.

Inhomogeneities affect the bulk physics introducing a Lagrangian
density along the impurity line, according to (). A
relevant and a marginal interactions will be the object of our
study in order to derive explicit expressions for the reflection
and transmission amplitudes.

